<dl id="n09029c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09029c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09029c"> 29(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> zigzag v spiral / corsi ricorsi Vico, <small>color t.b.a.</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09029c"><li>FW 481.02 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n09029c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n09029c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n09029c">MS BL 47482b-79</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:033 <a name="rA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/rA2d.htm#n09029c">Draft: III&sect;3A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Il n&apos;y a qu&apos;une seule loi, celle du progr&egrave;s&hellip; Au-dessus de toutes les lois auxquelles les anciens et les modernes ont tent&eacute; d&apos;assujettir les mouvements de l&apos;humanit&eacute;, au-dessus de tous les cycles, de toutes les alternatives, de tous les flux et reflux, de toutes les lignes droites ou bris&eacute;es, <mark>en spirale ou en zigzag</mark>, de tous les rythmes, itus reditusque, comme dit Pascal, <mark>corsi e ricorsi, comme dit Vico</mark>, il n&apos;y a que cette seule loi de progr&egrave;s qui pour ainsi dire surnage &hellip;. <br><font color="green">[There is only one law, progress &hellip; Over all the laws to which the ancients and the moderns have attempted to subjugate humanity&apos;s movements, over all the cycles and all the alternatives, all the ebbing and flowing, all the lines, whether straight or broken, in spirals or in zigzags, all the rhythms&mdash;itus reditusque, as Pascal said, corsi e recorsi, as Vico said&mdash;this single law of progress alone remains afloat, so to speak.]</font> <small> L&eacute;on Metchnikoff, <a name="LMCG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMCG"><cite title="source">La Civilisation et les grands fleuves Historiques</cite></a> (1889) 8</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Crossout faint. L. <i>Itus reditusque</i>, returning movement. It. <i>Corsi e ricorsi</i>, flow and return.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c03074c" href="c3all.htm#c03074c">VI.C.03:074(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
